      "writtenOn": "2015-12-11T13:39:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "bug: That\u0027s actually incorrect, a timeout of zero is not what you want here, it will return immediately if the connection doesn\u0027t happen immediately, which is possible, even on localhost!!\n\nWorse, this function can be used from a non-blocking socket (where the caller expects to handle the failures / wait itself). This call will reset it to blocking on return!\n\nYou might want to use negative timeout values, or INT_MAX instead to indicate waiting / blocking for the connect, and treat that differently in connect_with_timeout() !!",
      "revId": "bfcab8139fe97d607faee3b6e577110c4695cbfb",
